<section id="applications" class="py-14 border-b border-border">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
        <span class="section-rule"></span>
        <h2 class="mb-6">Application Guide by Closure Type</h2>

        <figure class="mb-8 -mx-6 sm:mx-0">
            <img
                src="/images/bottle-caps.jpg"
                alt="Assorted plastic closure caps in various sizes and colors used across beverage, dairy, and pharmaceutical packaging"
                class="w-full h-48 sm:h-56 object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
            />
            <figcaption class="mt-2 px-6 sm:px-0 font-mono text-[0.68rem] text-ink-faint">Closure caps span a wide range of diameters, materials, and tamper-evident configurations. Photo: Pexels</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <div>
            <div class="app-entry">
                <span class="app-code">PCO-1881-T</span>
                <h3>28mm <a href="https://www.isbt.com/resources/isbt-threadspecs" rel="noopener" target="_blank">PCO 1881</a> (Tethered)</h3>
                <p>Tethered closure format required by the <a href="https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/2019/904/oj" rel="noopener" target="_blank">EU Single-Use Plastics Directive</a> (SUPD). Chuck bore must clear the hinge band and tether link without interference during thread application. This means a modified internal bore profile compared to standard 28mm PCO tooling.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="app-entry">
                <span class="app-code">HDPE-38</span>
                <h3>38mm HDPE Dairy &amp; Juice</h3>
                <p>Wide-mouth HDPE closures for dairy, juice, and smoothie containers. The 38mm thread diameter demands high-grip knurl engagement in the chuck. Typical application torque runs 2.0 to 4.5 N·m with foil-seal compression verification.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="app-entry">
                <span class="app-code">ROPP</span>
                <h3>Roll-On Pilfer-Proof</h3>
                <p>Aluminum ROPP closures for spirits, wine, olive oil, and pharmaceutical syrups. The headset carries a top-pressure pad, threading rollers, and pilfer-band forming tools. Thread profile gets plastically formed onto the bottle finish, so roller geometry has to match the glass finish thread helix exactly.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="app-entry">
                <span class="app-code">CRC</span>
                <h3>Child-Resistant Closures</h3>
                <p>Pharmaceutical and household chemical push-turn and squeeze-turn CRC formats. The chuck applies axial load and rotational torque at the same time to engage the ratchet mechanism without over-torquing the inner seal. Torque verification per <a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-16/chapter-II/subchapter-E/part-1700" rel="noopener" target="_blank">16 CFR &sect;1700</a> (CPSC) is required.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="app-entry">
                <span class="app-code">SPORT</span>
                <h3>Sport / Pull-Push Closures</h3>
                <p>Pull-push and flip-top sport closures for bottled water, sports drinks, and personal care products. The chuck has to grip the closure body without touching the dispensing spout. Bore clearance is modified to accommodate the protruding nozzle and hinge tab.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="app-entry">
                <span class="app-code">TRIG-OC</span>
                <h3>Trigger Sprayer Overcaps</h3>
                <p>Overcap application for trigger sprayer assemblies on household cleaning and garden chemical containers. This is a snap-fit, not a threaded closure. The chuck applies controlled axial press-on force (top-load) rather than torque.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
